{"account":{"apiProvider":"firstParty","email":"kocienda@mac.com","organization":"kocienda@mac.com's Organization","subscriptionType":"Claude Max"},"agents":[],"available_output_styles":["default","Proactive","Explanatory","Learning"],"commands":[{"argumentHint":"","description":"Analyze recent work, stage relevant files, and create a git commit with a clear, informative commit message. (project)","name":"commit"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Deep research harness — fan-out web searches, fetch sources, adversarially verify claims, synthesize a cited report. (dynamic workflow)","name":"deep-research"},{"argumentHint":"[recipe-path]","description":"(tugplug) Bake a recipe (an implementation plan) into a tested build on an isolated worktree — agentless, in-thread, committing per step, stopping for review before merge","name":"bake"},{"argumentHint":"[name] [instruction|status|join|release]","description":"(tugplug) Quick, recipe-less, worktree-isolated work — agentless, in-thread, committing per round, stopping for review before merge","name":"dash"},{"argumentHint":"[idea]","description":"(tugplug) Author a recipe (an implementation plan) in-thread — clarify the idea, write it against the tugplan skeleton, validate it — ready for /tugplug:bake","name":"recipe"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Use this skill to configure the Claude Code harness via settings.json. Automated behaviors (\"from now on when X\", \"each time X\", \"whenever X\", \"before/after X\") require hooks configured in settings.json - the harness executes these, not Claude, so memory/preferences cannot fulfill them. Also use for: permissions (\"allow X\", \"add permission\", \"move permission to\"), env vars (\"set X=Y\"), hook troubleshooting, or any changes to settings.json/settings.local.json files. Examples: \"allow npm commands\", \"add bq permission to global settings\", \"move permission to user settings\", \"set DEBUG=true\", \"when claude stops show X\". For simple settings like theme/model, suggest the /config command.","name":"update-config"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Verify that a code change actually does what it's supposed to by running the app and observing behavior. Use when asked to verify a PR, confirm a fix works, test a change manually, check that a feature works, or validate local changes before pushing.","name":"verify"},{"argumentHint":"[issue description]","description":"Enable debug logging for this session and help diagnose issues","name":"debug"},{"argumentHint":"[low|medium|high|xhigh|max|ultra] [--fix] [--comment] [<target>]","description":"Review the current diff for correctness bugs and reuse/simplification/efficiency cleanups at the given effort level (low/medium: fewer, high-confidence findings; high→max: broader coverage, may include uncertain findings; ultra: deep multi-agent review in the cloud). Pass --comment to post findings as inline PR comments, or --fix to apply the findings to the working tree after the review.","name":"code-review"},{"argumentHint":"[<target>]","description":"Review the changed code for reuse, simplification, efficiency, and altitude cleanups, then apply the fixes. Quality only — it does not hunt for bugs; use /code-review for that.","name":"simplify"},{"argumentHint":"<instruction>","description":"Research and plan a large-scale change, then execute it in parallel across 5–30 isolated worktree agents that each open a PR.","name":"batch"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Scan your transcripts for common read-only Bash and MCP tool calls, then add a prioritized allowlist to project .claude/settings.json to reduce permission prompts.","name":"fewer-permission-prompts"},{"argumentHint":"[interval] [prompt]","description":"Run a prompt or slash command on a recurring interval (e.g. /loop 5m /foo). Omit the interval to let the model self-pace.","name":"loop"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Create, update, list, or run scheduled remote agents (routines) that execute on a cron schedule.","name":"schedule"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Build, debug, and optimize Claude API / Anthropic SDK apps. Apps built with this skill should include prompt caching. Also handles migrating existing Claude API code between Claude model versions (4.5 → 4.6, 4.6 → 4.7, retired-model replacements).\nTRIGGER when: code imports `anthropic`/`@anthropic-ai/sdk`; user asks for the Claude API, Anthropic SDK, or Managed Agents; user adds/modifies/tunes a Claude feature (caching, thinking, compaction, tool use, batch, files, citations, memory) or model (Opus/Sonnet/Haiku) in a file; questions about prompt caching / cache hit rate in an Anthropic SDK project.\nSKIP: file imports `openai`/other-provider SDK, filename like `*-openai.py`/`*-generic.py`, provider-neutral code, general programming/ML.","name":"claude-api"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Launch and drive this project's app to see a change working. Use when asked to run, start, or screenshot the app, or to confirm a change works in the real app (not just tests). First looks for a project skill that already covers launching the app; otherwise falls back to built-in patterns per project type (CLI, server, TUI, Electron, browser-driven, library).","name":"run"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Author or improve the run-<unit> skill — a per-project skill that tells agents how to build, launch, and drive this project's app. Use when the user asks to set up the project, get it running, write run instructions, or verify build/run steps work from a clean environment.","name":"run-skill-generator"},{"argumentHint":"[name]","description":"Start a new session with empty context; previous session stays on disk (resumable with /resume)","name":"clear"},{"argumentHint":"<optional custom summarization instructions>","description":"Free up context by summarizing the conversation so far","name":"compact"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Show current context usage","name":"context"},{"argumentHint":"","description":"Dump the JS